OL,3,CGovernment acted unlawfully twice in
OL,4,Capproving climate plan, High Court
OL,5,Crules
OL,7,FThe government acted unlawfully by
OL,8,Fapproving a strategy to meet the UK's
OL,9,Fcarbon targets, a High Court judge in
OL,10,Fthe second defeat it has suffered over
OL,11,Fits climate policy.
OL,13,FThree environmental charities argued
OL,14,Fat a hearing in February that the then-
OL,15,Fsecretary of state, Grant Shapps,
OL,16,Facted unlawfully by approving the
OL,17,Fplans as he lacked information on
OL,18,Fwhether individual policies could be
OL,19,Fdelivered in full.
