OL,3,CGovernment acted unlawfully twice in
OL,4,Capproving climate plan, High Court
OL,5,Crules
OL,7,FIn a ruling on Friday, Mr Justice
OL,8,FSheldon ruled in their favour, stating
OL,9,Fthat Mr Shapps' decision was "simply
OL,10,Fnot justified by the evidence".
OL,12,FHe said: "If, as I have found, the
OL,13,FSecretary of State did make his
OL,14,Fdecision on the assumption that each
OL,15,Fof the proposals and policies would be
OL,16,Fdelivered in full, then the Secretary
OL,17,Fof State's decision was taken on the
OL,18,Fbasis of a mistaken understanding of
OL,19,Fthe true factual position."
